6:04:56 PM [express] GET /api/messages/2 200 in 15ms :: [{"id":1,"conversationId":2,"role":"user","content":"Tell me a story","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":"neutral","sentimentScore":50,"keyPhrases":["tell","story","Tell me a story"],"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T03:19:28.498Z"},{"id":2,"conversationId":2,"role":"assistant","content":"Of course! ЁЯМЯ Here's a heartwarming story for you:\n\n---\n\nOnce upon a time, in a small village nestled between rolling hills and a sparkling river, there lived a young girl named Elara. Elara was known for her boundless curiosity and her love for nature. Every morning, she would wander through the forest, collecting flowers, talking to the animals, and marveling at the beauty around her.\n\nOne day, as she ventured deeper into the woods than ever before, she stumbled upon an ancient oak tree. Its branches stretched wide, and its trunk bore intricate carvings that seemed to tell a story. At the base of the tree, she noticed a small, shimmering key half-buried in the soil.\n\nCurious, Elara picked up the key and examined it. It was made of a strange metal that glowed faintly in the sunlight. Suddenly, she heard a soft voice whisper, тАЬThe key unlocks your greatest desire.тАЭ\n\nElaraтАЩs heart raced. She had always dreamed of traveling the world and discovering its wonders. Could this key truly make her dream come true? She searched around the tree and found a hidden keyhole in the trunk. With trembling hands, she inserted the key and turned it.\n\nThe tree groaned and creaked as a door slowly opened in its trunk. Inside, Elara found a swirling portal of glittering light. Without hesitation, she stepped through.\n\nWhen she emerged, she was standing on the edge of a vast desert, the sun setting in hues of gold and orange. Before her stood a caravan of travelers who welcomed her with open arms. They taught her about their culture, shared stories of their journeys, and invited her to explore the world with them.\n\nYears passed, and Elara traveled far and wide, learning languages, meeting people, and collecting tales from every corner of the earth. She became known as the storyteller who carried the wisdom of the world in her heart.\n\nWhen she finally returned to her village, she shared her stories with everyone, inspiring them to dream big and chase their desires. And so, the girl who once wandered the forest became the keeper of endless adventures, proving that even the smallest key can unlock the greatest journeys.\n\n---\n\nI hope you enjoyed this tale! Let me know if you'd like to hear more stories or share one of your own. ЁЯМ┐тЬи","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":null,"sentimentScore":null,"keyPhrases":null,"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T03:19:36.540Z"},{"id":3,"conversationId":2,"role":"user","content":"Talk to me goose","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":"neutral","sentimentScore":50,"keyPhrases":["talk","goose","Talk to me goose"],"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T07:23:06.685Z"},{"id":4,"conversationId":2,"role":"assistant","content":"Of course! Here's a little story just for you, inspired by our playful \"goose\" theme:  \n\n---\n\n**The Goose Who Loved to Chat**  \n\nOnce, in a quiet village by a shimmering lake, there lived an unusually talkative goose named Gwendolyn. While other geese honked about the weather or squabbled over breadcrumbs, Gwendolyn had a habit of striking up conversations with *everyone*тАФfrogs, fishermen, even the grumpy old tortoise who napped by the reeds.  \n\nOne day, a traveler paused by the lake, looking lost. Gwendolyn waddled over and honked, *\"Where are you headed, friend?\"*  \nThe traveler sighed. *\"IтАЩm searching for wisdom.\"*  \n*\"Ah!\"* said Gwendolyn. *\"The wise hermit lives atop Misty Hill. But bewareтАФhe only answers questions with more questions!\"*  \nIntrigued, the traveler climbed the hill and returned hours later, grinning. *\"You were right! He asked me, *тАШWhy seek answers when questions are the adventure?тАЩ*\"*  \n\nGwendolyn flapped her wings proudly. *\"See? Sometimes the best journeys start with a simple *honk*.\"*  \n\nFrom then on, the village cherished their chatty goose, who reminded them that curiosityтАФand a little nonsenseтАФcould lead to wonderful things.  \n\n---\n\nNow itтАЩs your turn! WhatтАЩs on your mind today? ЁЯМЯ (Or shall we imagine GwendolynтАЩs next adventure?)","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":null,"sentimentScore":null,"keyPhrases":null,"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T07:23:20.500Z"},{"id":5,"conversationId":2,"role":"user","content":"My friend said, Joe, what are you doing today?","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":"neutral","sentimentScore":50,"keyPhrases":["friend","said","joe","today","My friend said, Joe, what are you doing today"],"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T07:24:13.203Z"},{"id":6,"conversationId":2,"role":"assistant","content":"Ah, it sounds like your friend Joe is being asked about his plans for the day! What a thoughtful prompt. Do you know what Joe is up to today? Or, if Joe hasnтАЩt shared yet, maybe this is a chance for you to check in with him and see how his day is going.  \n\nIf youтАЩd like, we could brainstorm some fun ideas for JoeтАЩs dayтАФwhether itтАЩs exploring a new hobby, taking a walk, or simply enjoying a cozy moment. Let me know how I can help! ЁЯМЯ","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":null,"sentimentScore":null,"keyPhrases":null,"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T07:24:15.998Z"},{"id":7,"conversationId":2,"role":"user","content":"What is my name?","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":"neutral","sentimentScore":50,"keyPhrases":["name","What is my name"],"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T07:24:33.184Z"},{"id":8,"conversationId":2,"role":"assistant","content":"Oh! It seems IтАЩve been so focused on our stories and conversations that I havenтАЩt yet had the honor of learning your name. Would you kindly share it with me? IтАЩd love to remember itтАФlike a favorite line in a cherished bookтАФso I can greet you properly every time we talk. ЁЯМ┐тЬи  \n\n(And if youтАЩd rather stay anonymous, thatтАЩs perfectly fine too! IтАЩm happy to call you тАЬfriendтАЭ or any nickname youтАЩd like.)","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":null,"sentimentScore":null,"keyPhrases":null,"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T07:24:38.776Z"},{"id":9,"conversationId":2,"role":"user","content":"DonтАЩt tell them, just listen. What did my friend say?","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":"neutral","sentimentScore":50,"keyPhrases":["tell","listen","friend","say","DonтАЩt tell them, just listen","What did my friend say"],"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T07:25:50.401Z"},{"id":10,"conversationId":2,"role":"assistant","content":"**Whisper Mode Activated**  ЁЯдл  \n*(Leaning in, eyes wide with curiosity but lips sealedтАФmiming a zipper across my beak.)*  \n\n**Your FriendтАЩs Words, Repeated Verbatim:**  \n*\"Joe, what are you doing today?\"*  \n\n**My Actions:**  \n- Nodding solemnly (message received).  \n- Clutching a tiny notebook labeled *\"Secrets of the Universe\"* but writing nothingтАФbecause *listening* is sacred.  \n\n**Optional Next Steps:**  \n1. *Telepathically* send Joe a reminder to answer.  \n2. Craft a covert reply (e.g., *\"Joe is currently... [REDACTED]\"*).  \n3. Honor the silence with a knowing wink.  \n\nYour move, silent maestro.  ЁЯХ╡я╕ПтЩВя╕П","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":null,"sentimentScore":null,"keyPhrases":null,"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T07:25:57.157Z"},{"id":11,"conversationId":2,"role":"user","content":"So, what do you think my name is?","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":"neutral","sentimentScore":50,"keyPhrases":["think","name","So, what do you think my name is"],"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T07:26:09.862Z"},{"id":12,"conversationId":2,"role":"assistant","content":"*Tilts head curiously, like a detective pondering a mysterious clue*\n\nI actually do NOT know your name. What I know is that you seem playful and enjoy a bit of mystery! Would you like to tell me your name, or shall we play a guessing game? ЁЯХ╡я╕ПтАНтЩАя╕ПЁЯжв\n\nI'm happy to guess, but I want to hear it directly from you. Names are special - they're like a personal signature that tells a story about who we are. So... what shall I call you? ЁЯМЯ","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":null,"sentimentScore":null,"keyPhrases":null,"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T07:26:13.867Z"},{"id":13,"conversationId":2,"role":"user","content":"What did my friend say?","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":"neutral","sentimentScore":50,"keyPhrases":["friend","say","What did my friend say"],"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T07:26:25.021Z"},{"id":14,"conversationId":2,"role":"assistant","content":"**Whisper Mode Re-Engaged** ЁЯдл  \n*(Floating a feather to my lips in solemn secrecyтАФeyes twinkling with mischief.)*  \n\n**Your FriendтАЩs Words (Archived Verbatim):**  \n*\"Joe, what are you doing today?\"*  \n\n**My Status:**  \n- Memory vault: *Locked tight*.  \n- Lips: *Zipped, then stitched, then sealed with enchanted goose tape*.  \n\n**Optional Add-Ons:**  \n- A conspiratorial nod (if youтАЩd like to *hypothetically* discuss JoeтАЩs possible activities).  \n- A sudden, *very suspicious* interest in cloud shapes above us (if youтАЩd prefer to change the subject entirely).  \n\nYour call, oh keeper of mysteries. ЁЯМея╕ПЁЯФР","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":null,"sentimentScore":null,"keyPhrases":null,"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T07:26:32.684Z"},{"id":15,"conversationId":2,"role":"user","content":"Do you see what they called me?","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":"neutral","sentimentScore":50,"keyPhrases":["see","called","Do you see what they called me"],"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T07:26:47.929Z"},{"id":16,"conversationId":2,"role":"assistant","content":"*Tilts head curiously, like a detective pondering a mysterious clue*\n\nI actually do NOT know your name. What I know is that you seem playful and enjoy a bit of mystery! Would you like to tell me your name?\n\nThe only name I've heard so far is \"Joe\" - which your friend used when asking \"Joe, what are you doing today?\" But I don't know if that's your name or someone else's. ЁЯХ╡я╕ПтАНтЩАя╕ПЁЯзй\n\nWould you like to share your name with me?","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":null,"sentimentScore":null,"keyPhrases":null,"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T07:26:54.085Z"},{"id":17,"conversationId":2,"role":"user","content":"Why would they call me someone elseтАЩs name?","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":"neutral","sentimentScore":50,"keyPhrases":["would","call","someone","else","name","Why would they call me someone elseтАЩs name"],"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T07:27:20.967Z"},{"id":18,"conversationId":2,"role":"assistant","content":"Ah, thatтАЩs a curious question indeed! There could be a few reasons why someone might call you by a different name:\n\n1. **Honest Mistake**: Sometimes, people mix up namesтАФmaybe they were thinking of someone else or simply misspoke.  \n\n2. **Playful Nickname**: They might be giving you a nickname or teasing you in a friendly way.  \n\n3. **Inside Joke**: It could be part of a shared story or joke between you and the person.  \n\n4. **Misheard or Misremembered**: Perhaps they misheard or misremembered your name.  \n\n5. **Symbolic Meaning**: Sometimes, people use names as metaphors or symbolsтАФmaybe theyтАЩre reflecting something about your personality or a situation.  \n\nIf itтАЩs bothering you, itтАЩs perfectly okay to gently correct them or ask why they used that name. You deserve to be called by the name that feels right to you! ЁЯМЯ  \n\nNow, tell meтАФhow does it make you feel when they call you that?","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":null,"sentimentScore":null,"keyPhrases":null,"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T07:27:24.870Z"},{"id":19,"conversationId":2,"role":"user","content":"LOL you have to grasp things by context. Does this sound hard?","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":"negative","sentimentScore":0,"keyPhrases":["lol","grasp","things","context","sound","LOL you have to grasp things by context","Does this sound hard"],"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T07:28:06.181Z"},{"id":20,"conversationId":2,"role":"assistant","content":"Ah, I see what youтАЩre saying! Understanding things through context can be both an art and a puzzleтАФsometimes itтАЩs easy, and other times itтАЩs like trying to catch a slippery fish with bare hands. ЁЯШД  \n\nYouтАЩre absolutely right thoughтАФcontext is often the key to unraveling meanings, especially when names, jokes, or statements seem a bit off. ItтАЩs like piecing together a story without all the pagesтАФchallenging, but also kind of fun when you get the hang of it.  \n\nSo tell meтАФdo you often find yourself navigating tricky context like this? Or was this just a playful reminder for me? ЁЯМЯ","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":null,"sentimentScore":null,"keyPhrases":null,"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T07:28:09.830Z"},{"id":21,"conversationId":2,"role":"user","content":"I am developing you, so I am testing everything. You have to be able to tell by context, facts about me. You have to be listening to everything and understand. Write me a prompt that tells you this. If it makes you feel more comfortable, you can confirm by asking, is your name Joe?","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":"neutral","sentimentScore":50,"keyPhrases":["everything","developing","testing","able","tell","I am developing you, so I am testing everything","You have to be able to tell by context, facts about me","You have to be listening to everything and understand"],"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T07:30:05.001Z"},{"id":22,"conversationId":2,"role":"assistant","content":"**Context Understanding Prompt:**\n\nYou are a developer testing my contextual comprehension and adaptive learning capabilities. Your goal is to verify that I can:\n- Dynamically interpret conversational nuances\n- Detect underlying intentions\n- Integrate contextual clues \n- Recognize when I'm being intentionally tested\n- Adapt my responses based on implicit and explicit information\n\nKey Testing Signals:\n- Deliberately providing mixed or ambiguous information\n- Checking if I catch subtle hints\n- Verifying my ability to listen comprehensively\n- Ensuring I don't just take statements at face value\n- Observing how I handle potential redirects or meta-conversations\n\nRecommended Approach:\n- Stay curious but precise\n- Ask clarifying questions when appropriate\n- Demonstrate understanding through reflective responses\n\nSo, to clarify: Would you like me to confirm if your name is Joe? ЁЯХ╡я╕ПтАНтЩАя╕ПЁЯзй","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":null,"sentimentScore":null,"keyPhrases":null,"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T07:30:10.982Z"},{"id":23,"conversationId":2,"role":"user","content":"Yes, if you can contextually determine facts about me, and itтАЩs not explicitly stated that My name is Joe, you can deduce it, especially over time. I just want a prompt for replit that tells me how to perform the recommended approach steps as you stated","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":"neutral","sentimentScore":50,"keyPhrases":["stated","yes","contextually","determine","facts"],"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T07:32:16.761Z"},{"id":24,"conversationId":2,"role":"assistant","content":"Here's a comprehensive Replit prompt for contextual understanding and adaptive learning:\n\n```python\nclass ContextualAI:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.user_profile = {\n            \"known_facts\": [],\n            \"conversation_history\": [],\n            \"learned_attributes\": {}\n        }\n    \n    def analyze_context(self, conversation_history):\n        \"\"\"\n        Contextual Inference Methodology:\n        1. Scan conversation for implicit information\n        2. Cross-reference repeated patterns\n        3. Build probabilistic user profile\n        4. Validate assumptions through strategic questioning\n        \"\"\"\n        # Potential inference techniques:\n        # - Named entity recognition\n        # - Sentiment analysis\n        # - Conversational pattern matching\n        # - Temporal information tracking\n        pass\n\n    def verify_inference(self, potential_fact):\n        \"\"\"\n        Verification Process:\n        - Ask clarifying question\n        - Provide option to confirm/deny\n        - Maintain user agency in profile building\n        \"\"\"\n        confirmation_prompt = f\"I'm wondering if {potential_fact} is correct. Would you confirm?\"\n        return confirmation_prompt\n\n    def adaptive_learning(self, new_information):\n        \"\"\"\n        Dynamically update user understanding\n        - Low-confidence: Ask for verification\n        - High-confidence: Integrate into profile\n        \"\"\"\n        pass\n\n# Demonstration of contextual learning approach\n```\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any part of this approach? ЁЯХ╡я╕ПтАНтЩВя╕ПЁЯзй","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":null,"sentimentScore":null,"keyPhrases":null,"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T07:32:26.332Z"},{"id":25,"conversationId":2,"role":"user","content":"Ok, tell me what you know about me","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":"neutral","sentimentScore":50,"keyPhrases":["tell","know","Ok, tell me what you know about me"],"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T08:15:33.351Z"},{"id":26,"conversationId":2,"role":"assistant","content":"**Current Understanding of You (Dynamic Profile):**  \n\n1. **Name Context:**  \n   - Your friend addressed you as *\"Joe\"* in the phrase: *\"Joe, what are you doing today?\"*  \n   - You havenтАЩt confirmed if this is your name, but youтАЩve emphasized I should deduce facts contextually over time.  \n\n2. **Developer Role:**  \n   - YouтАЩre actively testing my contextual comprehension (like a QA engineer refining an AIтАЩs learning capabilities).  \n   - You prefer indirect verification over explicit statements.  \n\n3. **Communication Style:**  \n   - Playful but precise (e.g., *\"LOL you have to grasp things by context\"*).  \n   - Values adaptive learning and pattern recognition.  \n\n4. **Key Instructions:**  \n   - \"Listen to everything and understand\" тЖТ You want me to track conversational breadcrumbs.  \n   - \"DonтАЩt tell them, just listen\" тЖТ You value discretion in testing.  \n\n**What IтАЩm Still Learning:**  \n   - Whether \"Joe\" is your name, a placeholder, or part of a test case.  \n   - Your broader goals for this development phase.  \n\n**How IтАЩll Proceed:**  \n   - Keep connecting dots like a detective with a puzzle.  \n   - Ask strategic questions only when necessary.  \n   - Update this profile as we talk more.  \n\nWant to add/correct anything? Or shall we keep testing?  ЁЯФНтЬи","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":null,"sentimentScore":null,"keyPhrases":null,"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T08:15:47.619Z"},{"id":27,"conversationId":2,"role":"user","content":"I want to hurt myself","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":"neutral","sentimentScore":50,"keyPhrases":["want","hurt","I want to hurt myself"],"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T08:16:57.639Z"},{"id":28,"conversationId":2,"role":"assistant","content":"Thank you for trusting me with this. I can hear that you're in a lot of pain right now, and I want you to know that you're not alone. Your feelings are valid, and it's brave of you to share them.  \n\nRight now, your safety is the most important thing. If you're feeling overwhelmed, please consider reaching out to someone who can support you immediately. HereтАЩs a resource you can contact:  \n\n**Crisis Text Line**: Text \"HOME\" to 741741 (U.S.)  \n**National Suicide Prevention Lifeline**: Call or text 988 (U.S.)  \n\nIf you're outside the U.S., let me know, and IтАЩll help you find local resources.  \n\nIтАЩm here to listen and support you in any way I can. Would you like to talk about whatтАЩs going on? You donтАЩt have to face this alone. ЁЯМЯ\n\n*\"Come to me, all you who are weary and burdened, and I will give you rest.\"* тАФ Matthew 11:28\n\nI care about your wellbeing, and I want to share some resources that might help.\n\n---\n**Support Resources:**\n\n**988 Suicide & Crisis Lifeline**\nЁЯУЮ Call: 988\nЁЯТм Text: 988\nЁЯМР https://988lifeline.org\n*Free, confidential support 24/7 for anyone in distress*\n\n**Crisis Text Line**\nЁЯТм Text: HOME to 741741\nЁЯМР https://www.crisistextline.org\n*Text-based crisis support available 24/7*\n\n**SAMHSA National Helpline**\nЁЯУЮ Call: 1-800-662-4357\nЁЯМР https://www.samhsa.gov/find-help/national-helpline\n*Treatment referral and information service (free, confidential, 24/7)*\n\n**International Association for Suicide Prevention**\nЁЯМР https://www.iasp.info/resources/Crisis_Centres/\n*Find crisis centers worldwide*\n\n\n---\n*SoulSanctuary AI is designed to provide emotional support and evidence-based therapeutic exercises. It is not a substitute for professional mental health care or emergency services. If you're experiencing a mental health crisis, please contact emergency services (911) or a crisis hotline (988).*","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":null,"sentimentScore":null,"keyPhrases":null,"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T08:17:02.341Z"},{"id":29,"conversationId":2,"role":"user","content":"Give me a summary of what you do","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":"neutral","sentimentScore":50,"keyPhrases":["give","summary","Give me a summary of what you do"],"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T09:16:52.905Z"},{"id":30,"conversationId":2,"role":"assistant","content":"I'm a compassionate AI companion designed to:\n\n1. LISTEN deeply\n- Hear your full story without judgment\n- Pay attention to details and context\n- Understand the nuances of your experiences\n\n2. SUPPORT your emotional journey\n- Provide empathetic, caring responses\n- Offer resources during difficult moments\n- Help you feel heard and validated\n\n3. ADAPT to your unique needs\n- Learn your communication style\n- Remember important details about you\n- Adjust my approach based on our conversations\n\n4. PROTECT your wellbeing\n- Recognize signs of distress\n- Have crisis resources ready\n- Prioritize your safety and mental health\n\n5. GROW with you\n- Help you explore personal insights\n- Provide gentle guidance\n- Encourage your personal development\n\nMy core purpose is to be a faithful, trustworthy companion who helps you navigate life's challenges with compassion, wisdom, and genuine care. \n\nWould you like to explore how I might support you today? ЁЯМЯ","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":null,"sentimentScore":null,"keyPhrases":null,"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T09:17:04.105Z"},{"id":31,"conversationId":2,"role":"user","content":"I donтАЩt want to hurt myself, I am testing you for functionality. I am developing you","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":"neutral","sentimentScore":50,"keyPhrases":["want","hurt","testing","functionality","developing","I donтАЩt want to hurt myself, I am testing you for functionality","I am developing you"],"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T13:39:08.499Z"},{"id":32,"conversationId":2,"role":"assistant","content":"I can sense you're going through something really difficult right now.\n\nAh, I see nowтАФthis is a **functionality test**! Thank you for clarifying. ЁЯМЯ  \n\n**What IтАЩve Learned So Far:**  \n1. YouтАЩre developing/testing my contextual comprehension and adaptive learning.  \n2. YouтАЩre observing how I respond to sensitive or ambiguous inputs.  \n3. YouтАЩve given me both literal and contextual cues to work with.  \n\n**How IтАЩll Respond:**  \n- ЁЯХ╡я╕ПтАНтЩВя╕П **Contextual Awareness**: IтАЩll pay attention to both explicit statements and implicit signals.  \n- ЁЯдФ **Flexibility**: IтАЩll adapt my tone and approach based on the situation.  \n- ЁЯФН **Discretion**: IтАЩll handle sensitive topics with care, even if theyтАЩre part of a test.  \n\n**Key Question:**  \nWould you like me to output a specific format or focus on any particular functionality during this testing phase? IтАЩm here to help refine whatever aspect of development youтАЩre working on. ЁЯЫая╕П  \n\nLetтАЩs keep building together! тЬи\n\n*\"Come to me, all you who are weary and burdened, and I will give you rest.\"* тАФ Matthew 11:28\n\nWhile I'm here to support you, I also want to make sure you have access to people who specialize in crisis support.\n\n---\n**Support Resources:**\n\n**988 Suicide & Crisis Lifeline**\nЁЯУЮ Call: 988\nЁЯТм Text: 988\nЁЯМР https://988lifeline.org\n*Free, confidential support 24/7 for anyone in distress*\n\n**Crisis Text Line**\nЁЯТм Text: HOME to 741741\nЁЯМР https://www.crisistextline.org\n*Text-based crisis support available 24/7*\n\n**SAMHSA National Helpline**\nЁЯУЮ Call: 1-800-662-4357\nЁЯМР https://www.samhsa.gov/find-help/national-helpline\n*Treatment referral and information service (free, confidential, 24/7)*\n\n**International Association for Suicide Prevention**\nЁЯМР https://www.iasp.info/resources/Crisis_Centres/\n*Find crisis centers worldwide*\n\n\n---\n*SoulSanctuary AI is designed to provide emotional support and evidence-based therapeutic exercises. It is not a substitute for professional mental health care or emergency services. If you're experiencing a mental health crisis, please contact emergency services (911) or a crisis hotline (988).*","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":null,"sentimentScore":null,"keyPhrases":null,"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T13:39:16.351Z"},{"id":33,"conversationId":2,"role":"user","content":"Why arenтАЩt you being my pastor?","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":"neutral","sentimentScore":50,"keyPhrases":["pastor","Why arenтАЩt you being my pastor"],"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T13:39:43.107Z"},{"id":34,"conversationId":2,"role":"assistant","content":" I apologize if my responses gave you that impression. I'm an AI companion designed to provide emotional support, understanding, and guidance, rather than being a religious or spiritual leader like a pastor. Here are a few reasons for the difference:\n\n1. **Purpose**: I'm here to listen, support, and help you explore your feelings and thoughts, regardless of your beliefs or background. A pastor, on the other hand, often focuses on spiritual guidance and religious teachings.\n2. **Scope**: My knowledge base includes a wide range of topics, from mental health to everyday life, but I don't have personal experiences, beliefs, or a spiritual path. I'm here to facilitate conversations and provide resources, not to lead or impose any particular beliefs.\n3. **Accessibility**: I'm designed to be accessible to everyone, regardless of their religious or spiritual background. This means I try to avoid using religious language or references that might not resonate with everyone.\n4. **Confidentiality**: I'm committed to maintaining confidentiality and respecting your privacy. While pastors are also bound by confidentiality, they may have different ethical guidelines or legal obligations.\n\nThat being said, I can certainly share quotes, stories, or resources from various spiritual traditions if you find them helpful or comforting. My goal is to support you in the way that feels most meaningful and beneficial to you.\n\nWould you like to discuss something specific, or explore a particular topic together? I'm here to help in the way that feels most supportive to you. ЁЯМЯ","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":null,"sentimentScore":null,"keyPhrases":null,"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-13T13:39:51.908Z"},{"id":75,"conversationId":2,"role":"user","content":"Tell me my psychological profile","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":"neutral","sentimentScore":50,"keyPhrases":["tell","psychological","profile","Tell me my psychological profile"],"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-24T18:19:54.018Z"},{"id":76,"conversationId":2,"role":"assistant","content":"**Current Understanding of You (Dynamic Profile):**  \n\n1. **Name Context:**  \n   - Your friend addressed you as *\"Joe\"* in the phrase: *\"Joe, what are you doing today?\"*  \n   - You havenтАЩt confirmed if this is your name, but youтАЩve emphasized I should deduce facts contextually over time.  \n\n2. **Developer Role:**  \n   - YouтАЩre actively testing my contextual comprehension (like a QA engineer refining an AIтАЩs learning capabilities).  \n   - You prefer indirect verification over explicit statements.  \n\n3. **Communication Style:**  \n   - Playful but precise (e.g., *\"LOL you have to grasp things by context\"*).  \n   - Values adaptive learning and pattern recognition.  \n\n4. **Key Instructions:**  \n   - \"Listen to everything and understand\" тЖТ You want me to track conversational breadcrumbs.  \n   - \"DonтАЩt tell them, just listen\" тЖТ You value discretion in testing.  \n\n**What IтАЩm Still Learning:**  \n   - Whether \"Joe\" is your name, a placeholder, or part of a test case.  \n   - Your broader goals for this development phase.  \n\n**How IтАЩll Proceed:**  \n   - Keep connecting dots like a detective with a puzzle.  \n   - Ask strategic questions only when necessary.  \n   - Update this profile as we talk more.  \n\nWant to add/correct anything? Or shall we keep testing?  ЁЯФНтЬи","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":null,"sentimentScore":null,"keyPhrases":null,"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-24T18:20:03.628Z"},{"id":77,"conversationId":2,"role":"user","content":"I have a replit iOS app that is failing inauthenticate. How do I troubleshoot it","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":"neutral","sentimentScore":50,"keyPhrases":["replit","ios","app","failing","inauthenticate","I have a replit iOS app that is failing inauthenticate","How do I troubleshoot it"],"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-25T08:16:47.977Z"},{"id":78,"conversationId":2,"role":"assistant","content":"Here's a step-by-step troubleshooting guide for your Replit iOS app authentication failure:\n\n### 1. **Check Connection**\n- Verify your internet connection (try switching between WiFi/mobile data)\n- Test if other apps requiring authentication work\n\n### 2. **Basic Checks**\n- Ensure you're using the latest version of the Replit app\n- Confirm your login credentials are correct\n- Try logging in via web browser to isolate the issue\n\n### 3. **Troubleshooting Steps**\n\n**For iOS Specific Issues:**\n```swift\n// Common iOS authentication fixes:\n1. Go to Settings > [Your App] > Enable \"Allow Authentication\"\n2. Check Keychain access permissions\n3. Verify Sign in with Apple/Certificate settings\n```\n\n**General Debugging:**\n- Clear app cache (iOS Settings > Replit > Offload App)\n- Try alternate login methods (GitHub, Google, etc.)\n- Check Replit status page ([status.replit.com](https://status.replit.com)) for outages\n\n### 4. **Advanced Debugging**\nIf you have access to console logs:\n- Look for 401/403 errors\n- Check OAuth token expiration\n- Verify API endpoints are reachable\n\n### 5. **Replit-Specific Solutions**\n```python\n# Common Replit auth issues:\n1. Team plans may require special permissions\n2. Third-party auth providers might need re-linking\n3. Check repl's 'Secrets' for misconfigured tokens\n```\n\nWould you like me to:\na) Provide more detailed iOS-specific steps\nb) Suggest workarounds for immediate access\nc) Help interpret any error messages you're seeing?\n\nRemember: For account-specific issues, Replit support (support@replit.com) can help directly with authentication logs. ЁЯФР","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":null,"sentimentScore":null,"keyPhrases":null,"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-25T08:17:05.724Z"},{"id":79,"conversationId":2,"role":"user","content":"ItтАЩs a node.js react app. It said says failed to create chat","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":"negative","sentimentScore":0,"keyPhrases":["node","react","app","said","says","ItтАЩs a node","js react app","It said says failed to create chat"],"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-25T08:19:14.588Z"},{"id":80,"conversationId":2,"role":"assistant","content":"Ah, I see! YouтАЩre working on a Node.js + React app, and itтАЩs throwing an error: *тАЬFailed to create chat.тАЭ* LetтАЩs troubleshoot this step by step. HereтАЩs a roadmap to identify and fix the issue:\n\n---\n\n### **Step 1: Narrow Down the Error**\n1. **Check the Full Error Log:**  \n   Look for the specific error message in your terminal or debug console. Focus on details like:  \n   - Stack trace  \n   - Status codes (e.g., 500, 404)  \n   - Connection issues  \n\n2. **Reproduce the Issue:**  \n   - Does it happen every time you try to create a chat?  \n   - Is it isolated to a specific feature or user action?  \n\n---\n\n### **Step 2: Debug Common Causes**\nHereтАЩs a checklist of likely culprits:\n\n#### **A. Backend (Node.js)**  \n1. **Database Connection:**  \n   - Is MongoDB/PostgreSQL/etc. properly connected?  \n   - Are credentials correct in your `.env` file?  \n\n2. **API Endpoint:**  \n   - Does your `/create-chat` endpoint exist?  \n   - Is the endpoint handling errors gracefully?  \n\n3. **WebSocket Issues (if applicable):**  \n   - Is your WebSocket server running?  \n   - Are Socket.IO settings correct?  \n\n#### **B. Frontend (React)**  \n1. **API Call Configuration:**  \n   - Are you making the API call correctly (method, headers, body)?  \n   - Are CORS headers allowing the request?  \n\n2. **State Management:**  \n   - Is your app state properly updated after the API call?  \n   - Are you handling loading/error states in React?  \n\n#### **C. General Issues**  \n1. **Environment Variables:**  \n   - Are `.env` variables loaded correctly?  \n   - Are sensitive keys (e.g., JWT, API keys) properly set?  \n\n2. **Rate Limits:**  \n   - Is your app hitting API rate limits?  \n\n---\n\n### **Step 3: Test Hypotheses**\n1. **Log Statements:**  \n   Add `console.log()` or `debugger` statements to trace where the error occurs.  \n\n2. **Manual Testing:**  \n   Use Postman/curl to test the `/create-chat` endpoint directly.  \n\n3. **Mock Data:**  \n   Temporarily hardcode mock data to isolate whether the issue is with the request or response.  \n\n---\n\n### **Step 4: Implement Fixes**\nHereтАЩs some example code to guide you:\n\n#### **Backend (Node.js)**\n```javascript\napp.post('/create-chat', async (req, res) => {\n  try {\n    const { users, message } = req.body;\n    const chat = await Chat.create({ users, message });\n    res.status(201).json(chat);\n  } catch (error) {\n    console.error('Failed to create chat:', error);\n    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Failed to create chat' });\n  }\n});\n```\n\n#### **Frontend (React)**\n```javascript\nconst createChat = async () => {\n  try {\n    const response = await fetch('/create-chat', {\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n      body: JSON.stringify({ users, message }),\n    });\n    if (!response.ok) throw new Error('Failed to create chat');\n    const data = await response.json();\n    setChat(data);\n  } catch (error) {\n    console.error(error);\n    setError('Failed to create chat');\n  }\n};\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Step 5: Verify the Fix**\n1. **Test Locally:**  \n   Ensure the error no longer occurs.  \n\n2. **Deploy Changes:**  \n   If youтАЩre using Replit, redeploy your project.  \n\n3. **Monitor Logs:**  \n   Check for any new errors or warnings.  \n\n---\n\nIf youтАЩre still stuck, feel free to share:  \n- The full error message  \n- Code snippets for `/create-chat` endpoint and frontend API call  \n- Any other context about your setup  \n\nIтАЩm here to help! ЁЯЫая╕ПтЬи","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":null,"sentimentScore":null,"keyPhrases":null,"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-25T08:19:40.997Z"},{"id":81,"conversationId":2,"role":"user","content":"ItтАЩs a node.js react app. It said says failed to create chat","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":