PI routes         |\n\n### **2. Quick Checks**\n```bash\n# Verify Node.js version\nnode -v\n\n# Check if dependencies are installed\nnpm ls socket.io express mongoose\n```\n\n### **3. Specific Debugging Steps**\n**For iOS Simulator Issues:**\n```swift\n// In Xcode:\n1. Check Console logs (тМШ + тЗз + C)\n2. Verify \"Allow Arbitrary Loads\" in Info.plist:\n   <key>NSAppTransportSecurity</key>\n   <dict>\n      <key>NSAllowsArbitraryLoads</key>\n      <true/>\n   </dict>\n```\n\n**Backend (Node.js) - Sample Fix:**\n```javascript\n// In server.js\nconst io = require('socket.io')(server, {\n  cors: {\n    origin: \"http://localhost:3000\", // Update with your client URL\n    methods: [\"GET\", \"POST\"]\n  }\n});\n```\n\n**Frontend (React) - Connection Test:**\n```javascript\n// In App.js\nuseEffect(() => {\n  const socket = io('http://your-server-ip:3001', { \n    transports: ['websocket'] \n  });\n  \n  socket.on('connect_error', (err) => {\n    console.log('Connection error:', err);\n  });\n}, []);\n```\n\n### **4. What to Share for Faster Help**\nIf you can provide:\n1. The **exact error message** (screenshot/text)\n2. Relevant **code snippets** from:\n   - Backend route handling chat creation\n   - Frontend API call\n3. Any **unusual warnings** in Xcode console\n\nI can give you a more targeted solution! ЁЯЫая╕П\n\nWould you like me to:\n- Suggest specific Xcode project settings?\n- Help analyze logs?\n- Provide a sample chat implementation?","originalContent":null,"wasObfuscated":false,"sentiment":null,"sentimentScore":null,"keyPhrases":null,"hasAttachment":false,"attachmentType":null,"timestamp":"2025-12-25T08:22:36.417Z"}]
